        "Description": {
            "val": "The line item supports procurement of items such as equipment, modification kits, gear, relocatable trailers, livable containers, and material with a unit cost under $5M in support of the Marine Corps. \n\nMotor Transport Modifications - Funds procurement and modifications to ground transportation systems for operational priorities, vehicles, engineering change proposals, safety concerns, support equipment inefficiencies, tool malfunctions, product quality deficiencies, and other issues that affect reliability, availability, maintainability, and readiness. Provides for the procurement, sustainment, and life-cycle management of vehicles to implement improvements in response to known and emergent needs of the Marine Corps.\n\nMarine Security Guard (Vehicles) - Funds the procurement of commercial vehicles for the Marine Security Guard based on the requirements of the particular command and country embassies."
        },
        "Justification": {
            "val": "The FY 2016 funding request was reduced by $4.339M to account for the availability of prior year execution balances.\n\nFY 2014 Base Appropriation: $10.587M\nMotor Transport Modifications - $2.856M Provided for the implementation of the fleet service life extension initiatives, quality deficiency resolutions, safety initiatives, environmental\/state transportation mandated vehicle changes, and system component refresh modernization efforts.  Funding supported efforts such as adapting MTVR Trailer to accommodate up to two operating generators.  Modifications included improvements to enhance safety & reliability of the Internally Transportable Vehicle (ITV) System.\n\nMarine Security Guard (Vehicles) - $7.731M Procured vehicles for the Marine Security Guard.  These vehicles are varied in unit cost and range to include unarmored and armored SUVs.  Note:  There are multiple contract awards for these vehicles.\n\nFY 2015 Base Appropriation: $11.023M\nMotor Transport Modifications - $2.964M Provides for the implementation of the fleet service life extension initiatives, vehicles, quality deficiency resolutions, safety initiatives, environmental\/state transportation mandated vehicle changes, and system component refresh modernization efforts.  Funding supports modifications for medium and heavy lift trailers.  Improvements include, but are not limited to, axels, rims, hubs, suspension, tires and survivability kits for underbody protection.  Funding will support ITV improvements.\n\nMarine Security Guard (Vehicles) - $8.059M Procures vehicles for the Marine Security Guard.  These vehicles are varied in unit cost and range to include unarmored and armored SUVs.\n\nFY 2016 Base Appropriation Request: $6.938M\nMotor Transport Modifications - $1.108M will provide for the implementation of the fleet service life extension initiatives, vehicles, quality deficiency resolutions, safety initiatives, environmental\/state transportation mandated vehicle changes, and system component refresh modernization efforts.  Funding supports modifications for medium and heavy lift trailers.  Improvements include, but are not limited to, axels, rims, hubs, suspension, tires and survivability kits for underbody protection.  Provides support for initial integration, testing and fielding efforts for hosted systems i.e. C4I, weapons, and intel, that  use light tactical vehicles as their base transportation mode. Additional efforts include updates to technical data and procuring HMMWV ambulance conversion kits. The decrease  ($1.856M) from FY15 to FY16 is due to elimination of system modifications based on overall Service prioritizations.\n\nMarine Security Guard (Vehicles) - $5.830M Will procure vehicles for the Marine Security Guard.  These vehicles are varied in unit cost and range to include unarmored and armored SUVs. The decrease ($2.229M) from FY15 to FY16 is due to a decrease in the number of vehicles being procured based on the current requirements."
        },
